====Verb====
{{en-verb|lays|laying|laid}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To place down in a position of rest, or in a horizontal position.
#* '''1735''', author unknown, ''The New-England Primer'', as reported by Fred R. Shapiro in ''The Yale Book of Quotations'' (2006), Yale University Press, pages 549–550:
#*: Now I '''lay''' me down to sleep, / I pray the Lord my Soul to keep. / If I should die before I ’wake, / I pray the Lord my Soul to take.
#:: A corresponding intransitive version of this word is [[lie#Etymology_1|lie]]
# {{context|transitive|archaic|lang=en}} To cause to [[subside]] or [[abate]].
#* '''1590''', {{w|Edmund Spenser}}, ''The Faerie Queene'', II.viii:
#*: The cloudes, as things affrayd, before him flye; / But all so soone as his outrageous powre / Is '''layd''', they fiercely then begin to shoure [...].
#* '''1662''', Thomas Salusbury, ''Galileo's Dialogue Concerning the Two World Systems'', Dialogue 2:
#*: But how upon the winds being '''laid''', doth the ship cease to move?
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To leave something somewhere.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[prepare]] (a plan, project etc.); to [[set out]], [[establish]] (a law, principle).
#* '''2006''', {{w|Clive James}}, ''North Face of Soho'', Picador 2007, p. 48:
#*: Even when I '''lay''' a long plan, it is never in the expectation that I will live to see it fulfilled.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To install certain building materials, laying one thing on top of another.
#: '''''lay''' brick''
#: '''''lay''' flooring''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To produce and deposit an egg.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[wager]] that an event will not take place.
# {{context|transitive|slang|lang=en}} To [[have sex]] with.
#* '''1944''', {{w|Raymond Chandler}}, ''The Lady in the Lake'', Penguin 2011, p. 11:
#*: ‘It's because he's a no-good son of a bitch who thinks it is smart to '''lay''' his friends' wives and brag about it.’
# {{context|intransitive|nonstandard|lang=en}} to [[lie]] {{gloss|be in a horizontal or resting position}}
# {{context|nautical|lang=en}} To take a position; to come or go.
#: ''to '''lay''' forward; to '''lay''' aloft''

